entities.name: ElizaOS
entities.description: An AI agent platform that enables building agents that interact across platforms like Discord, Twitter, and Telegram. Users can create custom actions, add knowledge bases, and integrate with crypto functionality. The platform allows for both local and cloud-based agent hosting. It is currently preparing for its V2 release.

entities.name: Swarm
entities.description: A feature of ElizaOS that allows for multi-agent teams to self-complete tasks, enabling complex agent coordination.

entities.name: Dynamic Memory
entities.description: A feature of ElizaOS V2 that allows AI agents to recall preferences and past interactions.

entities.name: Enhanced TEE
entities.description: A feature of ElizaOS V2 involving secure enclave transaction processing.

entities.name: Agent-to-Agent marketplace
entities.description: A new concept within ElizaOS where AI agents can autonomously transact with each other, potentially creating a new type of digital economy. AI16Z tokens are planned as the settlement currency.

entities.name: GitHub
entities.description: A web-based platform for version control and collaboration, offering distributed version control using Git. It is a popular platform for hosting software development projects.

entities.name: AI16Z
entities.description: A token planned to be used as the settlement currency within the Agent-to-Agent marketplace on ElizaOS.

entities.name: Mattermost
